British Open Increases Champion’s Prize Money to $1.43 Million

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-25T14:44:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/british-open-increases-champion-s-prize-money-to-1-43-million.html
The winner of next month’s British
Open will receive $1.43 million, a 5 percent increase over
last year, organizers said.  The total purse at Royal St. George’s in Sandwich,  England ,
will rise to $7.98 million from $7.66 million last year, the
Royal and Ancient Golf Club of  St. Andrews , which runs golf’s
oldest major championship, said in a statement.  South African Louis Oosthuizen earned $1.37 million at
current exchange rates for winning the 2010 Open at St. Andrews
in Scotland. The British Open will be played July 14-17.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  